{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:57:13.939883+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b31dcaee641dae642e277a9d9dd36222f3ddc362)", "id": "lc_3ccc66fd-2399-4da8-8e8d-67a8f6494c9a"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Thin wrappers around git subprocess calls used by gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\n\n\ndef _git(*args: str) -> str:\n    return subprocess.check_output([\"git\", *args], text=True).strip()\n\n\ndef status_summary() -> str:\n    branch = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", \"HEAD\")\n    try:\n        upstream = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", f\"{branch}@{{upstream}}\")\n        ahead_behind = _git(\"rev-list\", \"--left-right\", \"--count\", f\"{upstream}...{branch}\")\n        behind, ahead = ahead_behind.split()\n        tracking = f\"(ahead {ahead}, behind {behind})\"\n    except subprocess.CalledProcessError:\n        tracking = \"(no upstream)\"\n\n    porcelain = _git(\"status\", \"--porcelain\").splitlines()\n    staged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[0] != \" \" and line[0] != \"?\")\n    unstaged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[1] != \" \")\n    untracked = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line.startswith(\"??\"))\n    return f\"{branch}  {tracking}  staged={staged} unstaged={unstaged} untracked={untracked}\"\n\n\ndef list_merged_branches(protected: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    out = _git(\"branch\", \"--merged\", \"main\")\n    branches = [line.strip().lstrip(\"* \").strip() for line in out.splitlines()]\n    return [b for b in branches if b and b not in protected]\n\n\ndef delete_branch(name: str) -> None:\n    subprocess.check_call([\"git\", \"branch\", \"-d\", name])\n", "id": "lc_c06b4929-ff83-4ad2-97ce-8c0a8d3dffa3"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "6a811da4-6893-42cb-b6a1-9417cfceef08", "tool_call_id": "call_36eb2c65021c42f5ab563903", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:57:20.211785+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what I found about this repository:\n\n## Command-Line Tool: `gwc`\n\nThe package installs a CLI tool called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion — described as \"small, local-only git helpers\").\n\nThe entry point is defined in `pyproject.toml` as:\n\n```\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\n## What `gwc` Currently Does\n\nThe `gwc` command supports **three subcommands**:\n\n| Subcommand | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `gwc status-summary` | Prints a one-line summary of the current branch state: branch name, tracking status (ahead/behind counts), plus counts of staged, unstaged, and untracked files. |\n| `gwc branch-name <issue_number> <slug>` | Generates a conventional branch name in the form `{prefix}{issue_number}-{slug}` (default prefix: `issue-`). |\n| `gwc clean-merged [--apply]` | Lists local branches fully merged into `main`. Runs as a **dry-run by default** (just prints what *would* be deleted). With `--apply`, it actually deletes those branches (skipping protected branches like `main` and `develop`). |\n\nUnder the hood, `gwc` shells out to `git` via `subprocess` (in `src/gwc/git_ops.py`) — it doesn't use any third-party dependencies.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 605, "prompt_tokens": 5110, "total_tokens": 5715, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 301, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4608, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002525824, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 8.31824e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0001694}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint